      "info": {
        "description": "Compartmental epidemic as a conservative primitive composition (Mobus process primitives, synchronous update mode). Susceptible, Infected, Recovered are Buffering stocks. An I-Sensor reads the Infected level through a non-draining observation flow and feeds a Message control into Susceptible; S's regulated release is the infection transfer S->I (gated by sensed I, drawn from S). Infected releases to Recovered at a constant recovery rate. The epidemic curve emerges entirely from the wiring; mass is conserved to machine epsilon. Seed storages via initial_state (S=100, I=5, R=0) and run with --update-mode synchronous.",
        "id": "S0",
